From: Ikey Doherty <ikey.doherty@lispysnake.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Aug 2020 15:31:02 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] m4/host-os: Do not define Serpent OS as 'GNU/Linux'

Serpent OS is built using a multitude of technologies and
origins, and the core toolchain is musl + LLVM projects.
While we do ship some GNU software (usually as dependencies
of another item of GNU software) we're not defined as
a GNU/Linux distribution, and are binary incompatible.

Let's dispell any misconceptions early of compatibility
that does not and will not exist.

Signed-off-by: Ikey Doherty <ikey.doherty@lispysnake.com>
---
 configure | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 65317b4..a9d12fb 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -39342,7 +39342,7 @@ else
        mint*)           os='MiNT';;
        mingw*)          os='MinGW';;
        lynxos*)         os='LynxOS';;
-       linux*)          os='GNU/Linux';;
+       linux*)          os='Linux';;
        hpux*)           os='HP-UX';;
        hiux*)           os='HI-UX';;
        gnu*)            os='GNU';;
